<subSubSection pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="209.[151,1437,1014,1725]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[265,511,1554,1581]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="1" refId="ref368514" refString="Rondani, C. (1859 b) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: III. Species italicae ordinis dipterorum in genera characteribus definita, ordinatim collectae, methodo analitica distinctae, et novis vel minus cognitis descriptis. Pars secunda: Muscidae, Siphoninae et (partim) Tachininae. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 243 + [1] p., 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1859">Rondani (1859b: 228)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[782,996,1554,1580]" genus="Sphixapata" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" rank="species" species="pelopei">
<emphasis box="[782,996,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Sphixapata pelopei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[1321,1407,1554,1580]" family="Number" pageId="209" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens and not giving a range of lengths, but presumably from more than 
<specimenCount box="[1074,1227,1590,1617]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
because he wrote: “ 
<emphasis box="[212,310,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">non rara</emphasis>
[not rare]”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T." box="[448,627,1626,1653]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 22" refId="ref362772" refString="Pape, T. (1988) A revision of the Palaearctic Sarcophagidae (Diptera) described by C. Rondani. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Series A (Biology), 416, 1 - 22." type="journal article" year="1988">Pape (1988: 12)</bibRefCitation>
designated a 
<typeStatus box="[779,882,1626,1652]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[897,919,1626,1652]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) and 
<typeStatus box="[982,1144,1626,1652]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
(
<specimenCount box="[1159,1225,1626,1653]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="male">2 ♂♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount box="[1236,1297,1626,1653]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="female">3 ♀♀</specimenCount>
) but did not mention an additional 
<specimenCount box="[452,636,1662,1688]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
: 
<specimenCount box="[647,749,1662,1689]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
in the MZUF, 
<specimenCount box="[918,1020,1662,1689]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
in the MSNC, and 
<specimenCount box="[1241,1365,1662,1689]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
in the MSNPV (all are 
<typeStatus box="[388,555,1698,1725]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
).
</paragraph>
